# CODEOWNERS intentionally has no active path rules.
#
# GitHub auto-requests review from CODEOWNERS on every PR touching
# matching paths, even when `require_code_owner_reviews` is disabled in
# branch protection. For a solo + automation-driven project, that
# created unactionable notification noise on every mechanical
# release-please PR.
#
# Protection now comes from branch protection status checks instead:
# allowlist (repo-structure.yml), public-hygiene, secret-scan (gitleaks),
# and the build. Those gate merges without pinging a human.
#
# When the team grows, reintroduce specific owner rules here.
